Axiom:
  for all v0, (for all v1, (for all v2, (for all v3, (if v0 is an object and v1 is an object and v2 is an object and v3 is an object then (if the ordered pair of v0 and v2 is equal to the ordered pair of v1 and v3 then (v0 is equal to v1 and v2 is equal to v3))))))

Axiom:
  for all v0, (if v0 is a map then (v0 is a function iff the domain of v0 is a set))

Theorem:
  for all v0, (for all v1, (if v0 is a set and v1 is a class then (if for all v2, (if v2 is an element of v1 then v2 is an element of v0) then v1 is a set)))
Proof:
  C is a class and (if A is a set then C is a set) and for all v0, (v0 is an element of C iff (v0 is an element of A and v0 is an object and v0 is an element of B))
  C is a set and C is equal to B
Qed.

Signature:
  for all v0, (if v0 is an expression then truth holds)

Signature:
  for all v0, (if v0 is a variable then v0 is an expression)

Signature:
  for all v0, (if v0 is equal to \varzero then v0 is a variable)

Signature:
  for all v0, (if v0 is a variable then for all v1, (if v1 is an expression then for all v2, (if v2 is equal to \abs{ v0 }{ v1 } then v2 is an expression)))

Signature:
  for all v0, (for all v1, (if v0 is an expression and v1 is an expression then for all v2, (if v2 is equal to \app{ v0 }{ v1 } then v2 is an expression)))

Signature:
  for all v0, (if v0 is equal to \fix then (v0 is an expression and for all v1, (if v1 is an expression then \app{ v0 }{ v1 } is equal to \app{ v1 }{ \app{ v0 }{ v1 } })))

Signature:
  for all v0, (for all v1, (if v0 is an expression and v1 is an expression then for all v2, (if v2 is equal to v0 \impl v1 then v2 is an expression)))

Signature:
  for all v0, (if v0 is an expression then (if v0 is true then truth holds))

Axiom (beta_reduction):
  for all v0, (for all v1, (for all v2, (if v0 is an expression and v1 is an expression and v2 is a variable then \app{ \abs{ v2 }{ v2 \impl v1 } }{ v0 } is equal to v0 \impl v1)))

Axiom (reflexivity):
  for all v0, (if v0 is an expression then v0 \impl v0 is true)

Axiom (modus_ponens):
  for all v0, (for all v1, (if v0 is an expression and v1 is an expression then (if v0 is true and v0 \impl v1 is true then v1 is true)))

Axiom (strengthening):
  for all v0, (for all v1, (if v0 is an expression and v1 is an expression then (if v0 \impl v0 \impl v1 is true then v0 \impl v1 is true)))

Theorem (Curry_Paradox):
  for all v0, (if v0 is an expression then v0 is true)
Proof:
  E is an expression
  N is equal to \abs{ \varzero }{ \varzero \impl E } and X is equal to \app{ \fix }{ N }
  X is equal to \app{ N }{ X } and \app{ N }{ X } is equal to X \impl E
  X \impl X \impl E is true
  X \impl E is true
  X is true
  E is true
Qed.

